text: The 1986 Hi-Tec British Open Championships was held at the Dunnings Mill Squash Club in East Grinstead and the Wembley Conference Centre in London from 14–22 April 1986. Jahangir Khan won his fifth consecutive title defeating Ross Norman in the final. ==Seeds== ==Draw and results== ===Final=== Jahangir Khan beat Ross Norman 9-6 9-4 9-6 ===Section 1=== ===Section 2=== Glen Brumby (seeded 9) withdrew before the tournament and was replaced by Mohamed Awad ==References== Category:Men's British Open Squash Championships Men's British Open Championship Men's British Open Squash Championship Men's British Open Squash Men's British Open Squash Championship Category:Squash competitions in London
title: 1986 Men's British Open Squash Championship
